doc.after: Few terrestrial vertebrates live in Antarctica 59 Invertebrate life includes microscopic mites like the Alaskozetes antarcticus lice nematodes tardigrades rotifers krill and springtails The flightless midge Belgica antarctica up to 6 millimetres 0 2 in in size is the largest purely terrestrial animal in Antarctica 60 The snow petrel is one of only three birds that breed exclusively in Antarctica 61
